YOu Surpriſe me with the Baroccian Manuſcript, but much more with the Account of the Credit it has gotten. Its Admirers, I preſume, take it to be an excellent Tract upon R. B's word, and fancy (
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ) Providence was concerned in the diſcovery and Publication of this piece. I muſt confeſs Providence has of late been thought very buſie, but I can aſſure you that Treatiſe was known in my time, and deſpiſed too. The Reaſons you will meet with anon, and after a ſhort Examination, I dare be confident you will confeſs it deſerves no better uſage.
